Anh - Anh
cyanocobalamin
[ˌsʌɪənə(ʊ)kə'baləmɪn]
■ noun a form of vitamin B12, a cobalt-containing vitamin derived from liver, fish, and eggs, a deficiency of which can cause pernicious anaemia.
Origin
1950s: from cyano- and cobalamin (blend of cobalt and vitamin).

Từ điển Kỹ thuật (EN)
Lĩnh vực: y học
■ vitamin

sentences.en: Cobalamin/cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12) is a water - soluble vitamin.
sentences.vi: Cobalamin/cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12) là vitamin có thể hòa tan trong nước.

sentences.en: Cobalamin/cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12) is a water-soluble vitamin.
